Here is a multiple-choice question in JSON format.
{
    "question": "What is the output of the following code snippet?\n```python\ndef output(data):\n    if isinstance(data, int):\n        print('Integer')\n    elif isinstance(data, float):\n        print('Float')\n    elif isinstance(data, str):\n        print('String')\n    else:\n        print('Unknown')\noutput(3.14)\n```",
    "choices": [
        {
            "choice": "Integer",
            "correct": "false"
        },
        {
            "choice": "Float",
            "correct": "true"
        },
        {
            "choice": "String",
            "correct": "false"
        }
    ]
}

Are the distractors that are completely unique, or are they similar?
